ZH: 我们的日子一直过得很快。
EN: Our days have been passing by quickly.

ZH: 他们在一起度过了美好的日子。
EN: They spent wonderful days together.

ZH: 爸爸常说，青春的日子很快就过去了。
EN: My dad often says that youth flies by.

ZH: 真希望时间会停止，让我们永远留在这美好的日子里。
EN: I wish time would stop, so we can stay in these beautiful days forever.

ZH: 这几天的日子里，他一直在为考试而忙碌。
EN: He has been busy studying for the exam these days.

ZH: 我们都在为了更好的明天而努力着。
EN: We are all working hard for a better tomorrow.

ZH: 那段日子里，他每天都在沉思着未来的路该怎么走。
EN: During those days, he was contemplating which path to take in the future.

ZH: 即使我们分开了，我也会永远珍惜我们在一起的日子。
EN: Even if we are apart, I will always treasure the days we spent together.

ZH: 每一天的日子都是如此美好，让人忘记了生活中的烦恼。
EN: Each day is so beautiful that it makes you forget about the troubles in life.

ZH: 希望未来的日子会更加幸福和美好。
EN: I hope the days ahead will be happier and brighter.

ZH: 在这个小村庄里，日子过得很慢，但却很幸福。
EN: Life in this small village goes by slowly, but it's very happy.

ZH: 每一个日子都是一个新的开始。
EN: Every day is a new beginning.

ZH: 请珍惜现在的幸福日子，因为明天的事情没人能预料。
EN: Cherish the happy days now, because no one can predict what will happen tomorrow.

ZH: 每一个努力的日子都会让我们变得更加强大。
EN: Every day of hard work will make us stronger.

ZH: 我希望能拥有这样美好的日子，就算只是一刹那。
EN: I wish I could have such beautiful days, even if it's just for a moment.

ZH: 生活中的日子会有起起伏伏，只要坚强地走下去，就会找到方向。
EN: Life will have its ups and downs, but as long as you stay strong, you will find your way.

ZH: 爷爷在他的日子里经历了许多事情，但他一直乐观面对。
EN: Grandpa has gone through many things in his days, but he has always faced them with optimism.

ZH: 他告诉我，珍惜每一天的日子，因为时间很宝贵。
EN: He told me to cherish every day, because time is precious.

ZH: 长大后，我们依然会回忆那些无忧无虑的日子。
EN: As we grow older, we will still remember those carefree days.

ZH: 在这个小镇上，日子都很平淡，但却过得很充实。
EN: Life in this small town may be mundane, but it is fulfilling.
